               <p>WILLIAM WELLS. I lost a saw last Friday from a building at which I was at work in <placeName id="t18291029-241-crimeloc1363">Copenhagen-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18291029-241-crimeloc1363" type="placeName" value="Copenhagen-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18291029-241-crimeloc1363" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18291029-241-off1361 t18291029-241-crimeloc1363"></join>, between twelve o'clock and a quarter before one, while I was gone to dinner.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18291029-241-person1945">
                  ZECHARIAH 
                  PEELE
               <interp inst="t18291029-241-person1945" type="surname" value="PEELE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-241-person1945" type="given" value="ZECHARIAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-241-person1945" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a carpenter. I was working at the same place; the prosecutor's wife called me to look after a person who was coming out of the building; I went and saw the prisoner coming out and going away - I asked him what he wanted in the building; he said he was looking for a job; I saw he had something under his coat, and drew out this saw.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. COLLYER. Q. Was this in the house? A. No, in the street.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18291029-241-person1946">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BROWN EDWARDS
               <interp inst="t18291029-241-person1946" type="surname" value="BROWN EDWARDS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-241-person1946" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-241-person1946" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took the prisoner.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence I was looking for work, and saw this building not finished - there was no carpenter's bench nor tools, but this saw was on the floor; I thought some carpenter had left it by mistake, and I took it to take to the public-house to inquire what carpenter had been at work - the witness came and asked what I meant by stealing the saw: I said I meant to take it to a public-house.</p>
               <p>WILLIAM WELLS. I constantly work there - we generally leave our tools on the bench; they were not hid - I was at work up stairs - my bench was on the first floor.</p>
               <p>
